obo:ECO_0007695  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_819  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The 5-HT transporter (SERT) is an integral membrane protein that transports 5-HT into cells in a sodium and chloride-dependent manner.\n\nCOS-1 cells were transfected to transiently express mouse SERT. Transport of radiolabelled [H3]5-HT into COS-1 cells (Fig.2a) is dependent on the extracellular sodium (Fig.3b) and chloride (Fig.2c) concentration.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has \"serotonin transmembrane transporter activity\" and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (show with high-resolution technique). The inference to term 'neurotransmitter uptake (GO:0001504)' is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[P31652] SynGO ID 820 (PMID:10460242, EM). Experimental description: The mouse brain cDNA library, cloned in λZAP, was purchased from Stratagene." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2018-07-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_819" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

